Translator's notes — capability (SPEC v4), parser, and the NET data
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Concord can store and serve translator's notes, but it redistributes NONE of the
copyrighted notes themselves. Two distinct things, two distinct licenses:

  1. The NET notes parser (code). The parser that turns a user's legally-obtained
     NET Bible into the notes JSON Concord ingests is MIT-licensed, ported from
     kbennett2000/net-bible-study (as used by soap-journal). The parser is *code
     only*; it may live in this repository. Its output for the NET Bible is NOT.
     (As of v4 Slice 1 the parser has not yet been vendored — the notes-ingest
     capability is in place against a documented JSON contract; the parser port is
     a follow-up. See docs/v4/notes-ingest.md.)

  2. The NET text and notes (data). The New English Translation (NET Bible),
     including its translator's / study / text-critical notes, is:

         Copyright © Biblical Studies Press, L.L.C. All rights reserved.
         https://netbible.com/

     This material is NOT redistributable. It is never committed to this
     repository and never baked into the published Docker image. A user who
     legally owns the NET Bible supplies their own parsed notes JSON under the
     gitignored, dockerignored data/private/ tree and rebuilds Concord locally
     (see docs/v4/notes-ingest.md). The same applies to any other restricted
     translation's notes.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Restricted translations — data/private/
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Any translation or notes set under data/private/ is non-distributable, local-only,
and intentionally absent from this repository and the published image. The
data/private/ directory is excluded by BOTH .gitignore and .dockerignore (the
"dual-ignore" invariant, SPEC v4 §2) — the only barrier keeping "all rights
reserved" content out of the build context and the baked bible.db.
